result.execSummary:
The defendant Daric Nathan Eckstein was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Daric Nathan Eckstein is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Daric Nathan Eckstein was found guilty of Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Daric Nathan Eckstein in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Atty Hendee states plea agreement.  Defendant to enter plea to Ct 1 in 15CM61 and state will move to dismiss Ct 2 and charges in 15TR616.  Atty Gumz agrees.  Defendant enters No Contest plea to Ct 1 in 15CM61.  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court questions Atty Gumz.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct 1 in 15CM61.  Court will dismiss Ct 2 in 15CM61 and charges in 15TR616.

BY THE COURT:  *Defendant sentenced to serve 5 days in the Marquette County Jail, consecutive to any sentence he may be serving.  *Granted 2 days credit.  *Pay costs of $243.00.  *Bond on file to be applied.  Balance to be paid within 60 days.
